Asahi, IKF, Avon, K Sera Sera Fall After India Regulator’s Order

-- B y   P r a d e e p   K u r u p
-- 
2011-09-22T04:05:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/asahi-ikf-avon-k-sera-sera-fall-after-india-regulator-s-order.html
  Asahi Infrastructure & Projects
Ltd. (ACHF) ,  IKF Technologies Ltd. (IKF) , Avon Corp. and K Sera Sera Ltd.
fell in Mumbai trading after  India ’s capital markets regulator
barred the companies from issuing shares or other convertibles.  The  Securities and Exchange Board of India  also barred  CAT
Technologies Ltd. (CCRC) ,  Maars Software International Ltd. (MRSSI)  and  Cals
Refineries Ltd. (CALS)  after its initial investigation showed the seven
firms manipulated prices through sale of global depository
receipts.  CAT Technologies fell as much as 10 percent, Maars Software
declined 19 percent and Cals Refineries retreated 2.7 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Pradeep Kurup at 
 pkurup3@bloomberg.net  